# Field input library (PEP Web)

The **Field** preview page (`/preview/input-type`, sidebar label **Field**) is the single source of truth for field inputs. All layouts that include inputs must follow the three-section model below.

## Page structure (`InputTypePage.tsx`)

| Section | Purpose | Registry source |
|--------|---------|-----------------|
| **§1 Framework differences** | Programmer table: stock **shadcn** vs **PEP** overrides (height, elevation, hover/focus, shells). Describes §2 behaviour. | `FIELD_FRAMEWORK_DIFFERENCES` in `pep-web/src/data/field-input-registry.ts` |
| **§2 Input library** | Approved value types — **always pick from here** when creating layouts. | `FIELD_INPUT_ROWS` where `tier: 'library'` |
| **§3 New inputs (pending review)** | Prototypes not yet in the library. Use only when **no similar §2 input exists**. | `FIELD_INPUT_ROWS` where `tier: 'pending'` |

## Layout rules (mandatory)

1. **Before coding inputs in a layout**, read §1 on the Field page (or `FIELD_FRAMEWORK_DIFFERENCES` in the registry).
2. **Pick the matching §2 row** by Figma Value Type name / behaviour (Text, Select, Date, Multi, field-group variants, etc.).
3. **Compose** using existing primitives — `Input`, `Field`, `Button` + `inputSurfaceClassName`, `Calendar`, `Popover` — as shown in `InputTypePage.tsx` / `ValueTypeSurface`. Do **not** create parallel component files (e.g. `InputDate.tsx`) unless the user explicitly requests a new primitive.
4. **If no §2 match exists**, implement against a §3 pending row for review. Do **not** ship to production layouts until the row is promoted to §2.
5. **When promoting §3 → §2**: change `tier` to `'library'` in `field-input-registry.ts`, remove or archive `pendingNote`, and **add rows to `FIELD_FRAMEWORK_DIFFERENCES`** if the promotion introduces new PEP-vs-shadcn overrides.

## Styling (from §1)

- Shared chrome: `@/lib/input-surface-classes` → `inputSurfaceClassName`
- Height: **`h-9` (36px)** — keep the shadcn New York input height
- Elevation: no default field elevation; `hover:shadow-elevation-md`; focus removes elevation + ring
- Select-like shells: `Button variant="outline"` + `inputSurfaceClassName` (not a separate Select file)
- Semantic tokens only — no hardcoded hex

## Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `pep-web/src/data/field-input-registry.ts` | §1 notes + §2/§3 row tiers |
| `pep-web/src/pages/InputTypePage.tsx` | Field page UI + `ValueTypeSurface` compositions |
| `pep-web/src/lib/input-surface-classes.ts` | Shared input chrome |

## Future atom pages

The same **§1 notes / §2 library / §3 pending** pattern will apply to other atom preview pages (Button, Badge, etc.). Mirror this registry + rule structure when those pages are added.
